<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-21T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="156" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 U.S.S.R./126a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-21T18:00:00-04:00">September
                                    21, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>254. At his suggestion conversations were resumed with <persName corresp="#p_TAA1">Troyanovsky</persName> this morning and will be
                            continued after he communicates with Moscow. Will advise you fully when
                            we have talked with him again.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>